 PA\">PA</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">660a26</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ψελλιζόμενος τὴν Ἑλλάδα φωνήν</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0658.tlg001:8:15\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hld.\">Hld.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8.15</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>: metaph., of Empedocles and the early philosophers, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">speak indistinctly,</tr_> <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἃ ψελλίζεται λέγων Ἐμπεδοκλῆς</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg025.perseus-grc1:985a:5\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Arist.\">Arist.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Metaph.\">Metaph.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">985a5</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ψελλιζομένῃ ἔοικεν ἡ πρώτη φιλοσοφία περὶ πάντων</foreign> ib.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg025.perseus-grc1:993a:15\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">993a15</biblScope> </bibl>; of metals, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">hesitate</tr_> to alloy, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg013:328b:9\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Id.\">Id.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ GC\">GC</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">328b9</biblScope> </bibl>:—<gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"voice\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Act.\">Act.</a></gram> </gramGrp> is later in this sense, used of Aristotle, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Phld.\">Phld.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Rh.\">Rh.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=